hpnicfRpr.name: hpnicfRpr
hpnicfRpr.description: This MIB manages RPR(Resilient Packet Ring)interfaces by providing an operational table which controls parameters of each RPR interface and reports alarm conditions. A RPR ring is composed of two fiber rings: Outer and Inner.

HpnicfRprRingletID.name: HpnicfRprRingletID
HpnicfRprRingletID.description: Indicates the path on which data flow is selected. The valid value is ringlet0 and ringlet1. They indicate two RPR fiber rings. Ringlet0 refers to outer ring and ringlet1 refers to inner ring.
HpnicfRprRingletID.reference: IEEE 802.17 V3.3 Subclause 11.2.1.1 Span and ringlet parameterization.

HpnicfRprServiceClass.name: HpnicfRprServiceClass
HpnicfRprServiceClass.description: Indicates the service class of RPR. The valid value is ClassC, ClassB, ClassA1 and ClassA0.

hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineTable.name: hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineTable
hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineTable.description: This table contains the specs of RPR ring.

hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineEntry.name: hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineEntry
hpnicfRprMaxmumDefineEntry.description: The entry of RPR Maximum Table.

hpnicfRprMaxMumIfIndex.name: hpnicfRprMaxMumIfIndex
hpnicfRprMaxMumIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hpnicfRprMaxStationNumDefine.name: hpnicfRprMaxStationNumDefine
hpnicfRprMaxStationNumDefine.description: Max station number supported by RPR ring.

hpnicfRprMaxReservedRateDefine.name: hpnicfRprMaxReservedRateDefine
hpnicfRprMaxReservedRateDefine.description: Max reserved rate supported by each RPR ringlet. An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in units of 1,000,000 bits per second. If this object reports a value of 'n' then the speed of the interface is somewhere in the range of 'n-500,000' to 'n+499,999'. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

hpnicfRprTopoImageXTable.name: hpnicfRprTopoImageXTable
hpnicfRprTopoImageXTable.description: This table contains additional objects for the rprTopoImageTable in IEEE-802DOT17-RPR-MIB.

hpnicfRprTopoImageXEntry.name: hpnicfRprTopoImageXEntry
hpnicfRprTopoImageXEntry.description: Each entry contains information specific to a particular station on the ring. The table has at least one entry for the station itself, this entry indicates zero hops on each ringlet.

hpnicfRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus.name: hpnicfRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus
hpnicfRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus.description: The current edge status of the west span. If an edge exists,the hpnicfRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus is true. Otherwise, the hpnicfRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus is false.

hpnicfRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus.name: hpnicfRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus
hpnicfRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus.description: The current edge status of the east span. If an edge exists, the hpnicfRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus is true. Otherwise, the hpnicfRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus is false.

hpnicfRprTopoImageXStationName.name: hpnicfRprTopoImageXStationName
hpnicfRprTopoImageXStationName.description: The operator assigned station name. The operator can assigned it by hpnicfRprTopoImageXStationName.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountTable.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountTable
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountTable.description: The RPR Source Mac Count Table contains the cumulative sum of frames and octects from the particular source station.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountEntry.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountEntry
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Source Mac Count Table.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountIfIndex.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountIfIndex
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress.description: MAC address of the source station where the frames come from.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames.description: Frames received from a particular MAC address of source station.

hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets.name: hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets
hpnicfRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets.description: Octets received from a particular MAC address of source station.

hpnicfRprDestMacCountTable.name: hpnicfRprDestMacCountTable
hpnicfRprDestMacCountTable.description: The RPR Destination MAC Count Table contains the cumulative sum of frames and octects to the particular destination station.

hpnicfRprDestMacCountEntry.name: hpnicfRprDestMacCountEntry
hpnicfRprDestMacCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR MAC Destination Count Table.

hpnicfRprDestMacCountByDestAddress.name: hpnicfRprDestMacCountByDestAddress
hpnicfRprDestMacCountByDestAddress.description: MAC address of the destination station where the frames are sent to.

hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames.name: hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames
hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames.description: Frames sent to a particular MAC address of destination station.

hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets.name: hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets
hpnicfRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets.description: Octets sent to a particular MAC address of destination station.

hpnicfRprPktDropCountTable.name: hpnicfRprPktDropCountTable
hpnicfRprPktDropCountTable.description: The RPR Packet Drop Count Table contains the cumulative sum of packets dropped for congestion.

hpnicfRprPktDropCountEntry.name: hpnicfRprPktDropCountEntry
hpnicfRprPktDropCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Packet Drop Count Table.

hpnicfRprPktDropCntIfIndex.name: hpnicfRprPktDropCntIfIndex
hpnicfRprPktDropCntIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hpnicfRprPktDropCntRingletID.name: hpnicfRprPktDropCntRingletID
hpnicfRprPktDropCntRingletID.description: The RPR Ringlet of the station through which the packets transmit.

hpnicfRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops
hpnicfRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class A packets which transmit down from the host.

hpnicfRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops
hpnicfRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class A packets which transmit up to the host.

hpnicfRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops
hpnicfRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class B packets which transmit down from the host.

hpnicfRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops
hpnicfRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class B packets which transmit up to the host.

hpnicfRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops
hpnicfRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class C packets which transmit down from the host.

hpnicfRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops.name: hpnicfRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops
hpnicfRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class C packets which transmit up to the host.

hpnicfRprStaticRSTable.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSTable
hpnicfRprStaticRSTable.description: The RPR Static Ring Selection table contains the static ring selection information by the way of configuration.

hpnicfRprStaticRSEntry.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSEntry
hpnicfRprStaticRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Static Ring Selection table.

hpnicfRprStaticRSMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSMacAddress
hpnicfRprStaticRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the station on the ring.

hpnicfRprStaticRSRingletID.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSRingletID
hpnicfRprStaticRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from one station to another. Ringlet0 refers to outer ring, while ringlet1 does inner.

hpnicfRprStaticRSTtl.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSTtl
hpnicfRprStaticRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by the selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprStaticRSValid.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSValid
hpnicfRprStaticRSValid.description: The flag identify whether the configed ringlet is valid. If it is true, the configed ringlet is valid, otherwise it's invalid.

hpnicfRprStaticRSRowStatus.name: hpnicfRprStaticRSRowStatus
hpnicfRprStaticRSRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The status includes createAndGo, active and destroy.

hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTable.name: hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTable
hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTable.description: The RPR Ipv4Dynamic Ring Selection Table that contains the dynamic ring selection information by shortest path.

hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry.name: hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry
hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Ipv4Dynamic Ring Selection Table.

hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress
hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress.description: The Ipv4 MAC address of destination station on the ring.

hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID.name: hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID
hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl.name: hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl
hpnicfRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by the selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSTable.name: hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSTable

hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry.name: hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry
hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Ipv6 Ring Selection Table.

hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress
hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress.description: The Ipv6 MAC address of the destination station on the ring.

hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID.name: hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID
hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl.name: hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl
hpnicfRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTable.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTable
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTable.description: The RPR Ipv4 Overall Ring Selection Table that contains the overall and active ring selection infomation by dynamic ring selection and static ring selection.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSEntry.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSEntry
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Overall Ring Selection Table.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the destination station on the ring.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSType.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSType
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSType.description: The ring selection item type indicates static or dynamic.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTtl.name: hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTtl
hpnicfRprIpv4OverallRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSTable.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSTable
hpnicfRprVrrpRSTable.description: The RPR VRRP Ring Selection Table that contains the ring selection information when the vrrp group is configured.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSEntry.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSEntry
hpnicfRprVrrpRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR VRRP Ring Selection Table.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress
hpnicfRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress.description: The virtual MAC address of the staion in VRRP group.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSMacAddress
hpnicfRprVrrpRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the station that is the master in VRRP group.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSRingletID.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSRingletID
hpnicfRprVrrpRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hpnicfRprVrrpRSTtl.name: hpnicfRprVrrpRSTtl
hpnicfRprVrrpRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDTable.name: hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDTable
hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDTable.description: The RPR Default RingID Table specify the default ringID.

hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDEntry.name: hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDEntry
hpnicfRprDefaultRingIDEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Default RingID Table.

hpnicfRprDefaultConfigRingletID.name: hpnicfRprDefaultConfigRingletID
hpnicfRprDefaultConfigRingletID.description: The default identifier of the ring configured by user.

hpnicfRprDefaultActiveRingID.name: hpnicfRprDefaultActiveRingID
hpnicfRprDefaultActiveRingID.description: The identifier of the default ring which is active currently. The default ring configured by user may be inactive.

hpnicfRprDefectReportTable.name: hpnicfRprDefectReportTable
hpnicfRprDefectReportTable.description: The RPR Defect Report Table that contains the trap information on the ring.

hpnicfRprDefectReportEntry.name: hpnicfRprDefectReportEntry
hpnicfRprDefectReportEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Defect Report Table.

hpnicfRprDefectCurrentStatus.name: hpnicfRprDefectCurrentStatus
hpnicfRprDefectCurrentStatus.description: Indicates the current status of RPR ring. This attribute is used to notify the management system that alarms generate or clear about some RPR ring.

hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapTable.name: hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapTable
hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapTable.description: The Table is for Class Of Service and RPR Service Class Mapping.

hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapEntry.name: hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapEntry
hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapEntry.description: An entry in the COS to Service Class Map Table.

hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapType.name: hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapType
hpnicfRprPriority2ClassMapType.description: The type of Priority,include tag, mpls, ip.

hpnicfRprPriorityValue.name: hpnicfRprPriorityValue
hpnicfRprPriorityValue.description: The priority of tag,mpls and ip, the value range is 0~7.

hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigTable.name: hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigTable
hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigTable.description: The RPR Rate Limit Configuration Table that contains the rate limit infomation of RPR serviec class.

hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigEntry.name: hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigEntry
hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Rate Limit Configuration Table.

hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigRingletId.name: hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigRingletId
hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigRingletId.description: The identifier of the ring of RPR ringlet.

hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigValue.name: hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigValue
hpnicfRprRateLimitConfigValue.description: The value of rate-limit that configured for diffrent service class. The unit is permillage.

hpnicfRprMacLearnCfgEntry.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnCfgEntry
hpnicfRprMacLearnCfgEntry.description: The entry of RPR MAC Address Table.

hpnicfRprMacLearnRprMac.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnRprMac
hpnicfRprMacLearnRprMac.description: The MAC address of the RPR station.

hpnicfRprMacLearnType.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnType
hpnicfRprMacLearnType.description: The type of MAC address item that the user built. The type includes static and dynamic.

hpnicfRprMacLearnVlanId.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnVlanId
hpnicfRprMacLearnVlanId.description: The vlan ID that the MAC address learned from by RPR staion.

hpnicfRprMacLearnRinglet.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnRinglet
hpnicfRprMacLearnRinglet.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hpnicfRprMacLearnTtl.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnTtl
hpnicfRprMacLearnTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station on the selected ringlet.

hpnicfRprMacLearnIsValid.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnIsValid
hpnicfRprMacLearnIsValid.description: The flag identify whether the configured mac address is valid. If it is true, the configured mac address is valid, otherwise it's invalid.

hpnicfRprMacLearnRowStatus.name: hpnicfRprMacLearnRowStatus
hpnicfRprMacLearnRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The status includes createAndGo, active and destroy.

hpnicfRprTrapVarTable.name: hpnicfRprTrapVarTable
hpnicfRprTrapVarTable.description: The RPR Defect Report Table that contains varible that used to bind in trap.

hpnicfRprTrapVarEntry.name: hpnicfRprTrapVarEntry
hpnicfRprTrapVarEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Trap Var Table.

hpnicfRprTrapIfIndex.name: hpnicfRprTrapIfIndex
hpnicfRprTrapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of RPR interface. It is only used for trap to bind.

hpnicfRprTrapRinglet.name: hpnicfRprTrapRinglet
hpnicfRprTrapRinglet.description: The span of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hpnicfRprTrapTopoMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprTrapTopoMacAddress
hpnicfRprTrapTopoMacAddress.description: The MAC address of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hpnicfRprTrapIpAddress.name: hpnicfRprTrapIpAddress
hpnicfRprTrapIpAddress.description: The IP address of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hpnicfRprTopologyOpenRing.name: hpnicfRprTopologyOpenRing
hpnicfRprTopologyOpenRing.description: The topology openRing trap indicates that the RPR ring is opened.

hpnicfRprTopologyCloseRing.name: hpnicfRprTopologyCloseRing
hpnicfRprTopologyCloseRing.description: The topology openRing trap indicates that the RPR ring is closed.

hpnicfRprTopologyInconsistent.name: hpnicfRprTopologyInconsistent
hpnicfRprTopologyInconsistent.description: The topology inconsistent trap indicates that the topology of RPR is inconsistent.

hpnicfRprTopologyInstability.name: hpnicfRprTopologyInstability
hpnicfRprTopologyInstability.description: The topology instability trap indicates that the topology of RPR is instability.

hpnicfRprDuplicateMacAddress.name: hpnicfRprDuplicateMacAddress
hpnicfRprDuplicateMacAddress.description: The duplicate MAC address trap indicates that the mac address of the station on the ring is dulplicate. That means there is the same MAC address between two stations on the ring.

hpnicfRprDulplicateIPAddress.name: hpnicfRprDulplicateIPAddress
hpnicfRprDulplicateIPAddress.description: The dulplicate IP address trap indicates that the IP address of the station on the ring is dulplicate. That means there is the same IP address between two stations on the ring.

hpnicfRprIncompleteLRTT.name: hpnicfRprIncompleteLRTT
hpnicfRprIncompleteLRTT.description: The incomplete LRTT trap indicates that LRTT is not completed.

hpnicfRprProtecConfigInconsistent.name: hpnicfRprProtecConfigInconsistent
hpnicfRprProtecConfigInconsistent.description: The protection configuration inconsistent trap indicates that the configuration of protection mode on the ring is inconsistent. That is one station is configured steer mode while the other is configured wrap mode.

hpnicfRprJumboConfigInconsistent.name: hpnicfRprJumboConfigInconsistent
hpnicfRprJumboConfigInconsistent.description: The jumbo configuration inconsistent trap indicates that the configuration of jumbo mode on the ring is inconsistent. That is one station supports jumbo frame while the other doesn't support jumbo frame.

hpnicfRprExceedMaxReservRate.name: hpnicfRprExceedMaxReservRate
hpnicfRprExceedMaxReservRate.description: The exceeded max reserved rate trap indicates that the rate on the ringlet exceeded the max reserved rate. The operator can configure reserved rate for every station, but the sum of all stations' reserved rate of each RPR ringlet can't exceed maximum.

hpnicfRprExceedMaxStationNum.name: hpnicfRprExceedMaxStationNum
hpnicfRprExceedMaxStationNum.description: The exceeded max station number trap indicates that the number of the stations on the ring exceeded the max station number.

hpnicfRprMiscabling.name: hpnicfRprMiscabling
hpnicfRprMiscabling.description: The miscabling trap indicates that the miscabling event occurred.

hpnicfRprBackPressure.name: hpnicfRprBackPressure
hpnicfRprBackPressure.description: The back pressure trap indicates that the backpressure is generated on the ringlet. That is the data flow on the ringlet exceeded the range of rate-limit configured.

hpnicfRprBackPressureOver.name: hpnicfRprBackPressureOver
hpnicfRprBackPressureOver.description: The back pressure over trap indicates that the backpressure is disappeared on the ringlet.
